## Key Files and Their Purposes

### Configuration Files
- `components.json`: Shadcn/ui component configuration
- `next.config.js`: Next.js framework configuration
- `tailwind.config.ts`: Tailwind CSS styling configuration
- `tsconfig.json`: TypeScript compiler configuration
- `postcss.config.js`: PostCSS processing configuration

### Core Application Files
- `src/app/layout.tsx`: Root layout with providers and global structure
- `src/app/page.tsx`: Home page component
- `src/lib/prisma.ts`: Database client initialization
- `src/lib/authProvider.tsx`: Authentication context provider
- `src/lib/tanStackProvider.tsx`: Query client provider

### Data and State
- `src/queries/tripQueries.ts`: Trip data fetching logic
- `src/queries/userQueries.ts`: User data fetching logic
- `src/store/UserStore.ts`: Global user state management
- `src/hooks/useCurrentUser.ts`: Current user data hook

### Styling
- `src/app/globals.scss`: Global CSS styles
- `src/app/Home.module.scss`: Home page specific styles

## Development Guidelines

### File Organization
- Use kebab-case for directory names
- Use PascalCase for component files
- Use camelCase for utility and hook files
- Group related functionality in dedicated directories

### Component Structure
- Each component should have its own directory if it includes multiple files
- Include component-specific styles in the same directory
- Use index files for clean imports when appropriate

### API Routes
- Organize by resource type (auth, trips, users)
- Use dynamic routes for parameterized endpoints
- Follow RESTful conventions

### Database
- Keep migrations in chronological order
- Use descriptive migration names
- Maintain seed data for development

### Static Assets
- Use descriptive filenames for images and SVGs
- Optimize images for web delivery
- Keep assets organized by type or feature
